# Base Image
FROM debian:bullseye-slim

ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

# Dependencies that don't change with g2p updates and can be cached, and make it lean
run apt-get update -y \
    && apt-get install --no-install-recommends -y \
        apt-transport-https \
        libffi-dev \
        openssl \
        libssl-dev \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        python3-dev \
        build-essential \
        nano \
        git \
    && apt-get clean \
    && apt-get autoremove \
    && rm -fr /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Get g2p-specific dependencies that can also often be cached
RUN mkdir -p /g2p/g2p
COPY requirements /g2p/requirements
COPY requirements.txt /g2p
COPY setup.py /g2p
RUN python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip \
    && MAKEFLAGS="-j$(nproc)" pip3 --no-cache-dir install -r /g2p/requirements.txt

# Install g2p itself, last
COPY g2p /g2p/g2p
COPY README.md /g2p
COPY Dockerfile /g2p
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir -e /g2p

# Comment this out if you just want to install g2p in the container without running the studio.
CMD gunicorn --worker-class eventlet -w 1 g2p.app:APP --no-sendfile --bind 0.0.0.0:8000
